return if still unconfigured\n\n## Related Files\n- `/home/jeepney/.hermes/sessions/backup-verification-2026-05-24.json` (verification report)\n- `project_backup_phase2_scheduled_automation.md` (backup design)\n- `SOUL.md` § Hermes OAuth System-Wide Fix (2026-05-22)\n\n---\n**Status:** 🟡 Awaiting user action  \n**Last Updated:** 2026-05-25 02:30 KST\n","metadata":{"filePath":"/home/jeepney/.openclaw/workspace-dev/memory/hermes_backup_verification_status_2026_05_25.md","fileSize":2109,"lastModified":"2026-05-24T17:30:54.453Z"}}
{"id":"c4602261-84ef-464e-b6e3-2d6977235c5f","source":"memory-file","sourceFile":"hermes_claude_subscription_setup.md","timestamp":"2026-05-19T03:19:20.426Z","hash":"7c254e5d6e4b224be56770715fdb3fb616ed5449259fb1e542932ff6aaa55268","size":1628,"content":"---\nname: Hermes + Claude 구독 연결 (비공식)\ndescription: Claude Code OAuth 자격증명으로 Hermes 실행 — 비공식 호환 레이어 + 약관 위반 위험\ntype: reference\n---\n\n## 구조\n\nClaude Code 구독으로 Hermes 실행하기 — API key가 아니라 Claude Code 계정 OAuth 자격증명 사용.\n\n**단계:**\n1. Claude Code 로그인 → access/refresh token 저장 (Keychain 또는 `~/.claude/.credentials.json`)\n2. Hermes ops 프로필: `provider: anthropic, model: claude-opus-4-7`\n3. Hermes 실행 시 ANTHROPIC_API_KEY 대신 Claude Code OAuth token 읽음\n4. 요청이 Claude Code 구독 한도에서 차감됨\n\n**차이점:**\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` 환경변수 설정 → API 과금 경로 (구독 아님)\n- Claude Code OAuth token 사용 → 구독 한도 적용\n\n## 호환 레이어 (패치)\n\n일반 Anthropic 요청과 달리 Claude Code 요청 형태에 맞춰야 함.\n\n**패치 두 가지 역할:**\n1. System prompt, tool naming, beta flag, SDK header를 Claude Code 형태로 변환\n2. Keychain 만료 토큰 감지 → `~/.claude/.credentials.json` 유효한 token으로 fallback\n\n## 현재 ops 설정\n\n```yaml\nmodel:\n  provider: anthropic\n  default: claude-opus-4-7\n\nfallback_providers:\n  - provider: openai-codex\n    model: gpt-5.5\n```\n\n패치 위치: `/Users/deck/.hermes/patches` (update 후 유지됨)\n\n## 운영 주의점\n\n- **한도 공유:** Claude + Claude Code 사용량이 구독 한도 공유\n- **429 에러:** 설정 오류 아님, 실제 구독 한도/속도 제한 가능\n- **대용량 요청:** `claude-opus-4-7:1m` 또는 병렬 subagent는 한도 빠르게 소모\n- **완전 재설치:** venv `sitecustomize.py` 사라지면 patch loader 재설치 필요\n\n## 위험 & 책임 (⚠️)\n\n- **비공식 통합:** Claude Code CLI 공식 사용 경로가 아님\n- **약관 위반 가능성:** 제3자 런타임(Hermes)에서 OAuth 토큰 사용 — Anthropic 약관 확인 필요\n- **책임:** 사용자 책임 운영. 깨질 수 있고 계정 제한 받을 가능성 있음\n- **공유 금지:** 다른 사람에게 줄 때는 \"작동하지만 깨질 수 있고 약관/정책 리스크 있음\" 명시\n\n---\n\n## 저장된 구성\n\n**Hermes ops 프로필:** 로컬 hermes 설정에서 확인  \n**토큰 저장 경로:**\n- macOS Keychain (우선)\n- `~/.claude/.credentials.json` (fallback)\n\n패치는 Keychain 만료 토큰 제거 후 파일 토큰 시도.\n","metadata":{"filePath":"/home/jeepney/.openclaw/workspace-dev/memory/hermes_claude_subscription_setup.md","fileSize":2400,"lastModified":"2026-05-19T03:19:20.426Z"}}
{"id":"ba6f0b1d-31fc-41a6-aed2-a4f375c45f2c","source":"memory-file","sourceFile":"hermes_integration_architecture.md","timestamp":"2026-05-19T02:40:05.511Z","hash":"7161c8672bfe7aeb26ae2e4b63208b584f6222a1e9dec070436387e5d70510b9","size":9049,"content":"---\nname: Hermes ↔ OpenClaw Integration Architecture\ndescription: Parallel autonomous agent framework (Hermes) with OpenClaw coordination system for DSC Mannur plant automation\ntype: project\n---\n\n# Hermes ↔ OpenClaw Integration Architecture\n\n**Installation Date:** 2026-05-19 11:50 KST  \n**Installation Status:** ✅ Complete (v0.14.0)  \n**Environment:** WSL2 Ubuntu at `/home/jeepney/.openclaw/workspace-dev`  \n**User Mode:** Autonomous operation (vacation 2026-05-15~24)\n\n---\n\n## 1. System Overview\n\n### Current State\n- **OpenClaw:** Central command hub for DSC FMS portal (real-time coordination, team management, user-facing UI)\n- **Hermes:** Autonomous background agent framework (passive information gathering, automated reporting, scheduled tasks)\n- **Deployment:** Same PC (WSL2), parallel operation without interference\n\n### Why Parallel?\n- OpenClaw: Reactive (responds to user/team actions)\n- Hermes: Proactive (runs scheduled tasks autonomously)\n- Combined: Full-spectrum automation (command + autonomous background)\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Flow Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   DSC FMS Portal                         │\n│                  (OpenClaw layer)                        │\n│  - Real-time UI coordination                            │\n│  - Team task management (CTB)                           │\n│  - Phase A/B/C implementation                           │\n└────────────┬────────────────────────────────┬───────────┘\n             │                                │\n    ┌────────▼────────┐          ┌────────────▼────────┐\n    │   Supabase DB   │          │  Discord/Telegram   │\n    │  (Source of     │          │   (User I/O)        │\n    │    Truth)       │          │                     │\n    └─┬───────────────┘          └────────────┬────────┘\n      │                                       │\n      │                    ┌──────────────────┘\n      │                    │\n      │             ┌──────▼──────────────┐\n      │             │  Hermes Agent      │\n      │             │  (Autonomous Loop) │\n      │             │                    │\n      │             │  - Background jobs │\n      │             │  - Scheduled tasks │\n      │             │  - Auto-reporting  │\n      │             │  - Data gathering  │\n      │             └──────┬─────────────┘\n      │                    │\n      └────────────────────┴─ Sync via API/File\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Integration Points\n\n### 3.1 Data Ingestion (Hermes → Supabase)\n**Read from:** `memory/active_work_tracking.md`, DSC FMS Supabase tables  \n**Action:** Hermes cron jobs parse CTB, extract status snapshots  \n**Output:** `/home/jeepney/.hermes/sessions/` + auto-generated reports\n\n**Use Cases:**\n- Daily 08:00: Fetch pending blockers → Send Telegram summary\n- Daily 14:00: Parse Phase A checkpoints → Validate completion\n- Daily 18:00: Generate team capacity utilization report\n\n### 3.2 Task Delegation (OpenClaw → Hermes)\n**Trigger:** When OpenClaw task hits \"autonomous background loop\"  \n**Pattern:** Hermes skills handle pure information gathering (no writes to DB)  \n**Output:** Results written to `/home/jeepney/.hermes/sessions/` → read by OpenClaw\n\n**Example Flow:**\n```\nOpenClaw: \"Need daily asset health report\"\n  ↓\nHermes: Run `asset-health-check` skill (scheduled)\n  ↓\nOutput: JSON report → /home/jeepney/.hermes/sessions/asset-health-2026-05-19.json\n  ↓\nOpenClaw: Read file, format for Telegram, send to user\n```\n\n### 3.3 Messaging Coordination (OpenClaw ↔ Hermes)\n**Telegram/Discord Integration:**\n- OpenClaw remains primary message receiver\n- Hermes: Read-only passive listener (no direct sends to user)\n- Handoff: OpenClaw routes autonomous reports to user with Hermes origin tag\n\n**Tag Format:**\n```\n【Hermes 자동리포트】\n[Hermes Report]\n└─ Generated by: [skill-name]\n└─ Timestamp: 2026-05-19 08:15 KST\n└─ Data: [report content]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Shared Workspace Structure\n\n```\n/home/jeepney/.openclaw/workspace-dev/\n├── memory/\n│   ├── MEMORY.md (OpenClaw index)\n│   ├── active_work_tracking.md (CTB — read by Hermes)\n│   ├── hermes_integration_architecture.md (this file)\n│   └── hermes_autonomous_jobs.md (Hermes cron schedule)\n├── dsc-fms-portal/ (OpenClaw primary codebase)\n│\n/home/jeepney/.hermes/\n├── config.yaml (Hermes configuration)\n├── .env (API keys: OpenAI, Telegram, Discord)\n├── SOUL.md (Hermes personality/autonomous behavior)\n├── sessions/ (Hermes run logs + auto-generated reports)\n├── skills/ (88 bundled + custom skills)\n└── cron/ (scheduled autonomous jobs)\n```\n\n**Sync Point:** `/home/jeepney/.openclaw/workspace-dev/memory/` is readable by both  \n(Hermes reads CTB to understand current work state; OpenClaw ignores Hermes logs by design)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Autonomous Job Types (Hermes Cron)\n\n### Category A: Daily Status Snapshots (Read-Only)\n- **08:00 KST:** Parse CTB → Extract pending blockers → Auto-alert draft\n- **14:00 KST:** Validate Phase A milestone completion\n- **18:00 KST:** Team capacity utilization report\n\n### Category B: Scheduled Ba","metadata":{"filePath":"/home/jeepney/.openclaw/workspace-dev/memory/hermes_integration_architecture.md","fileSize":9979,"lastModified":"2026-05-19T02:40:05.511Z"}}
